Proxilion
=========

Proxilion is an MIT-licensed reverse proxy (and pre-flight advisor and audit
ingester) for managed AI agents acting against SaaS APIs.

Built on the PIC protocol.
--------------------------

The cryptography is not ours. Proxilion implements the **PIC protocol**
(Principal-bound Capabilities), designed and specified by **Nicola Gallo**
at https://pic-protocol.org/. PIC defines the PCA chain structure, the
monotonic ops-shrinkage invariant, and the Trust Plane signing model that
every guarantee in this repo depends on. If you find Proxilion useful,
please read and cite Nicola's work first.

Upstream Rust dependencies.
---------------------------

* `provenance-core` — federated trust framework implementing PIC.
    Clay Good (MIT)
    https://github.com/clay-good/provenance
    Pinned to a specific SHA in proxilion's Cargo.toml.

What Proxilion contributes on top of PIC.
-----------------------------------------

The deployable system *around* the protocol: the OAuth interception layer,
the Google Drive / Gmail / Calendar adapters, the YAML policy engine, the
audit and SIEM plumbing, the embedded admin UI, the operator CLI, and the
Rust reverse proxy itself.
